##_____________________________________________________________________________

@NODE ShellUsage "Using RunLame from a shell/CLI"

                  @{U}General notes on usage from a shell/CLI@{UU}

It's  assumed, that shell/CLI users are advanced and more experienced users.
If  you  don't  userstand  the  explanations  in  this  section, use RunLame
together with the @{"Workbench" LINK WorkbenchUsage}.

You  can  simply call RunLame using the command @{B}RunLame@{UB}. This opens the @{"GUI" LINK Option_GFXUSERINTERFACE}
and  configures  RunLame  according to it's @{"defaults" LINK Option_DEFAULTS}. If you don't need the
@{"GUI" LINK GUI_Explanation},  call RunLame together  with  the  needed  @{"switches" LINK ShellOptions}  and  the desired
@{"commandline" LINK Option_COMMANDLINE}.  Since RunLame  ignores  the Workbench @{"tooltypes" LINK WorkbenchTooltypes} when started
from  a  shell/CLI, shell users can only @{"configure" LINK Configuring} RunLame using aliases or
script files.

@ENDNODE
##_____________________________________________________________________________

@NODE ShellOptions "RunLame configuration on shell"

                             @{U}AmigaDOS template@{UU}

